<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I was recently in a Karnor's Castle group and stated early on when someone asked that loot rules were Need before Greed.  No one argued.  Later a jade mace dropped.  Suddenly the cleric, Frozu from the guild Vengeance, and a shaman named Ssik claimed that they needed a jade mace.  lol... I laughed at the claim that anyone but the main meleeing classes should be rolling on a jade mace.  They insisted on rolling and unfortunately the looter allowed their rolls to stand and handed the mace to the shaman.  Shamans and clerics claiming loot rights on this item is the biggest need before greed lie I've seen to date.  We're talking about a L50+ group here. Shamans and clerics NEED a 9/18 1hb with no other stats?  Bull.  That's like me, a warrior, claiming that I should roll on a nice pure wisdom item that drops so that I can do better at trade skills. Frozu actually tried to argue that he needed the mace to beat down greens that aggro him. lol... Pardon me, i'm very bitter.  I've hunted in KC for months.  I've killed around 40 drolvarg captains in my Live Tower camps and that's the only jade mace I've ever seen drop.  Then all of us meleers present get screwed out of it when loot rules were stated Need before Greed.  Apparently I must set up the loot rules for each and every item that could drop at that camp and tell everyone who joins the group what classes can roll on every single item that might drop.  Some people clearly are out to abuse "need before greed".  <P>Not that it's likely to happen, but if you're in a group with Frozu or Ssik, be sure to roll on every single item you could possibly equip that they want.  If it's a great wisdom item and you're a monk, don't let that deter you!  You want your brewing to be better, don't you?  Roll!  Think about that minotaur hero brew you've always wanted to make!  If you're a warrior and an item with the same AC but less weight drops, ignore the +50 mana that makes it obviously a caster item.  YOU NEED IT!  Roll!   If you can't even equip the item, you'll have to get more creative about why you need it.  I'll leave that to you. :-P<P>-- Callon Stormryder<BR>-- L54 Warrior / Rodcet Nife
</FONT>
